**What They Want From This Post:** To know which style of short French tip actually suits *their* nail shape — and to feel confident that short nails can look genuinely stylish, not like a compromise. They want real options beyond the classic white tip, curated for their length.

**What Satisfies Them:** Specific, shape-matched recommendations. Seeing their nail shape addressed directly. Learning *why* something works (proportion, curve, colour) not just being told it does. Coming away with a clear idea of what to book or buy.

**What Frustrates Them:** Posts full of long nail images labelled "short French" when the nails clearly aren't short. Generic advice ("any shape works!") that doesn't help them decide. Being shown almond as the answer when their nails are too short for almond. Roundups with no editorial filter — 34 images and nothing explained.

